   <text>
      <body>
         <div>
            <pb facs="#facs_1" n="1" xml:id="img_0001"/>
            <ab facs="#facs_1_r">
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_1" n="N001"/><Religion>Religion</Religion> + <Arts>art</Arts>
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l" n="N002"/>I. <hi style="text-decoration: underline;">Human nature and <Arts>art</Arts>.</hi>
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_2" n="N003"/>A. <Philosophy>Philosophy</Philosophy>, {and} the question of man and the
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_3" n="N004"/>question of <Being>being</Being>.
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_4" n="N005"/>B. Expression as an <Ontology>ontological</Ontology> category.
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_5" n="N006"/><Arts>Artistic</Arts> expression. Eros and expression.
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_6" n="N007"/>I. cont.
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_7" n="N008"/>C. Transformation as an anthropological category.
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_8" n="N009"/><Arts>Artistic</Arts> transformation.
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_9" n="N010"/>D. Anticipation as an <Ethics>ethical </Ethics>category.
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_10" n="N011"/><Arts>Artistic</Arts> anticipation.
            </ab>
            <pb facs="#facs_2" n="2" xml:id="img_0002"/>
            <ab facs="#facs_2_r">
               <lb facs="#facs_2_l" n="N001"/><hi style="text-decoration: underline;">II.<Culture> Culture</Culture>, <Society>society</Society> and <Arts>art</Arts></hi>
               <lb facs="#facs_2_l_1" n="N002"/>A. <Arts>Art</Arts> and homo Faber (so called pure art)
               <lb facs="#facs_2_l_2" n="N003"/>B. <Arts>Art </Arts>and knowledge (awareness and emotion)
               <lb facs="#facs_2_l_3" n="N004"/>C. <Arts>Art</Arts> and<Ethics> ethics</Ethics> (The aesthetic and the ethical
               <lb facs="#facs_2_l_4" n="N005"/>point of view.)
               <lb facs="#facs_2_l_5" n="N006"/>II. cont.
               <lb facs="#facs_2_l_6" n="N007"/>D. <Arts>Art</Arts> and <Society>social structures </Society>(Interdependence)
               <lb facs="#facs_2_l_7" n="N008"/>E. Social <Symbol>symbols</Symbol> and anticipation.
            </ab>
            <pb facs="#facs_3" n="3" xml:id="img_0003"/>
            <ab facs="#facs_3_r">
               <lb facs="#facs_3_l" n="N001"/><hi style="text-decoration: underline;">III. <Religion>Religion</Religion> and <Arts>Art</Arts>.</hi>
               <lb facs="#facs_3_l_1" n="N002"/><hi style="text-decoration: underline;">A. </hi>The first level: <Religion>Religion</Religion> and expression universally
               <lb facs="#facs_3_l_2" n="N003"/>B. The second level: <Religion>Religion</Religion> and <Expressionism>expressionistic</Expressionism>
               <lb facs="#facs_3_l_3" n="N004"/>expression
               <lb facs="#facs_3_l_4" n="N005"/>C. The third level. <Religion>Religion</Religion> expressed in its <Symbol>symbols</Symbol>
               <lb facs="#facs_3_l_5" n="N006"/>III. cont.
               <lb facs="#facs_3_l_6" n="N007"/>D. The 4 level: <Religion>Religious</Religion> style and <Religion>religious</Religion>
               <lb facs="#facs_3_l_7" n="N008"/>content. (The cult picture
            </ab>
            <pb facs="#facs_4" n="4" xml:id="img_0004"/>
            <ab facs="#facs_4_r">
               <lb facs="#facs_4_l" n="N001"/><hi style="text-decoration: underline;">Intr. Remarks</hi>
               <lb facs="#facs_4_l_1" n="N002"/>3. The double purpose: a] <Religion>Religion</Religion> and <Arts>Art</Arts>
               <lb facs="#facs_4_l_2" n="N003"/>b] <Religion>Religious </Religion>and<Arts> artistic</Arts> symbols.
               <lb facs="#facs_4_l_3" n="N004"/>1. The situation in the National Council and in Union 
               <lb facs="#facs_4_l_4" n="N005"/>2. Difference to former lectures: The double purpose
               <lb facs="#facs_4_l_5" n="N006"/>4 The infinity of material and the difficulty
               <lb facs="#facs_4_l_6" n="N007"/>of choice. (Each evening differently)
               <lb facs="#facs_4_l_7" n="N008"/>5. Three types of students a] Those who are interested.
               <lb facs="#facs_4_l_8" n="N009"/>b] Those who want to help {and to be helped}. c] Those
               <lb facs="#facs_4_l_9" n="N010"/>who work on problems of <Symbol>symbolism </Symbol>and be helped.
            </ab>
            <pb facs="#facs_5" n="5" xml:id="img_0005"/>
            <ab facs="#facs_5_r">
               <lb facs="#facs_5_l" n="N001"/><hi style="text-decoration: underline;">2</hi>
               <lb facs="#facs_5_l_1" n="N002"/>(Possibility of a smaller group. - <rs type="person" key=", tillich_person_id__1923">Hannah</rs>'s guiding trips)
               <lb facs="#facs_5_l_2" n="N003"/>6. Today the meaning of <Religion>religious</Religion> <Arts>art</Arts>. Pictures
               <lb facs="#facs_5_l_3" n="N004"/>{at random}.
            </ab>
         </div>
